                                                  java.util.function.Supplier<? extends HandlerMaps.Handler0<? super KT>> supplier)
        Add a new no-arg handler to the map.

        Allows the passing of handlers via lambdas.

        e.g. put(Some.class, SomeHandler::new)

        Where SomeHandler implements Handler0. This means SomeHandler does not count towards the classes data abstraction coupling

        Type Parameters:
        KT - the derived key type.
        Parameters:
        type - the key type to register the handler against
        supplier - the supplier of the handler. The supplier will be called immediately.
